ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I only took this class because I had to (degree requirement), and must say that it doesn't seem too relevant to the research I will be doing. For anybody interested in Logic, and who has taken a course in first order logic, I would definitely recommend this class. After this class you will understand not only what it means to say that first order logic is sound and complete, but you will actually know how to prove that. If you would like to know these things, it's exactly the right class for you. (But if you have a lot of math background already, it might be a bit too slow for you - it's mostly aimed at people like me with background in philosophy and not so much in math)
I would most recommend this course to someone with a math background and interests.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I don't think it really did; it doesn't have much to do with my future research. It might perhaps have taught me to think in more systematic ways.
Very little, I am afraid, but hopefully it sharpened my thinking skills.
